Proposed Tool: Automated Website Walkthrough Recorder

Purpose: Automatically generate a silent, 30-60 second screen recording of a clients tailored website, simulating a user clicking through key pages (e.g., homepage, about, services, contact). The video acts as a pitch to show clients what YeahBuddy built for them, hosted on a shareable link for easy delivery.

Tool Setup:

  • Platform: Cloud-based web app hosted on Vercel (free tier), using GitHub for version control to keep it low-maintenance and aligned with your preference for GitHub-based solutions.
  • Tech Stack:
    • Puppeteer: Navigates the website, simulates clicks, and captures a screen recording.
    • FFmpeg: Processes the recording into a polished MP4 video.
    • Vercel: Hosts a simple form to input the website URL and select pages to showcase.
    • Google Drive: Stores the video and generates a shareable link (free).
    • Monday Integration: Pulls client website URLs from the Monday Leads board and logs the video link back for easy tracking.
  • Workflow:
    1. In Mondays Leads board, select a client (e.g., Jos Bakery) with their tailored website URL (e.g., a YeahBuddy staging link like jo-bakery.yeahbuddy.nz).
    2. Open the Vercel app (via a Monday automation or bookmark) and input the URL and key pages to record (e.g., homepage, menu, contact).
    3. Puppeteer loads the site, clicks through the selected pages (e.g., 10 seconds per page), and records the screen.
    4. FFmpeg trims and formats the video (30-60 seconds, silent, MP4).
    5. The video uploads to Google Drive, and the shareable link is logged back in Monday.
    6. Send the video link to the client via Mondays email integration or a templated email, directing them to www.yeahbuddy.nz to choose pricing and go live.

Is Google Drive Paid?

Google Drive offers 15 GB of free storage with every Google account, shared across Drive, Gmail, and Google Photos. This is enough for most small businesses, especially for your use case of storing short, silent MP4 videos (30-60 seconds, ~10-50 MB each). You dont need to pay for Google Drive unless you exceed 15 GB, which would take hundreds of videos. Paid plans (Google One) start at $1.99/month for 100 GB if you ever need more. Since youre aiming for free, the 15 GB free tier should work fine for now, and you can manage storage by deleting old videos or using multiple free Google accounts if needed.

Keeping the Walkthrough Tool Free

  • Vercel: Free tier supports hosting the web app for your scale (unlimited API calls for small projects).

This will automate silent website click-throughs and screen recordings, saving time on client pitch videos while integrating with your Monday workflow.

Plan: Automated Website Walkthrough Recorder

Purpose: Generate a silent, 30-60 second MP4 video of a clients tailored website (e.g., jo-bakery.yeahbuddy.nz), clicking through key pages (homepage, services, about, contact). Videos are saved locally, uploaded manually to Google Drive (free), and logged in Monday for quick client pitches.

Why GitHub?

  • Free Hosting: GitHub Pages for the frontend (form to input URL and pages) and Vercel for the backend (Puppeteer/FFmpeg API) are free.
  • Version Control: GitHub keeps your code safe and lets you tweak it later.
  • Community Vibe: Fits YeahBuddys open, collaborative ethos.

Tool Setup:

  • Frontend: A simple HTML form (hosted on GitHub Pages) where you input the website URL and pages to record.
  • Backend: A Node.js API (hosted on Vercel) using Puppeteer for click-throughs and FFmpeg for screen recording.
  • Storage: Videos are saved locally (or to Vercels temp storage), then manually uploaded to Google Drives free 15 GB tier.
  • Monday Integration: Pull client URLs from Mondays Leads board and log video links back via manual entry or Zapiers free tier.

Workflow:

  1. In Mondays Leads board, pick a client (e.g., Jos Bakery, jo-bakery.yeahbuddy.nz).
  2. Open the GitHub Pages form, input the URL and pages (e.g., /, /services, /about, /contact).
  3. The Vercel API runs Puppeteer to navigate the site, click through pages, and record a silent video.
  4. FFmpeg formats the video (~30-50 MB, 30-60 seconds).
  5. Download the video from Vercel, upload it to Google Drive, and copy the shareable link.
  6. Log the link in Monday and email it to the client, directing them to www.yeahbuddy.nz for pricing.

Setup Steps (All Free)

  1. Create GitHub Repo:
    • Go to GitHub.com, sign up (free), and create a new repo (e.g., yeahbuddy-walkthrough).
    • Add two files:
      • index.html (from the first artifact) in the root for GitHub Pages.
      • api/walkthrough.js (from the second artifact) in an api folder for Vercel.
  2. Host Frontend on GitHub Pages:
    • In your repo, go to Settings Pages.
    • Set Source to Deploy from a branch, select the main branch, and save.
    • Wait ~5 minutes; your form will be live at https://yourusername.github.io/yeahbuddy-walkthrough.
    • Test the form by opening the URL and entering a test website (e.g., https://jo-bakery.yeahbuddy.nz).
  3. Host Backend on Vercel:
    • Sign up at Vercel.com (free) and connect your GitHub repo.
    • Create a new project, select your yeahbuddy-walkthrough repo, and deploy.
    • Add dependencies to a package.json in the repo root:
      json
      { "name": "yeahbuddy-walkthrough", "version": "1.0.0", "dependencies": { "puppeteer": "^23.0.0", "ffmpeg-static": "^5.0.0" } }
    • Set the API endpoint in the HTML form (replace https://your-vercel-app.vercel.app with your Vercel URL, e.g., https://yeahbuddy-walkthrough.vercel.app).
    • Test the API by submitting the form; it should download a video file.
  4. Google Drive:
    • Use a free Google account with 15 GB storage.
    • After downloading the video from the form, upload it to Google Drive.
    • Right-click, select Share, and copy the shareable link (e.g., drive.google.com/file/jos-bakery-walkthrough).
    • Store ~300-500 videos (30-50 MB each) in the 15 GB limit; delete old ones to stay free.
  5. Monday Integration:
    • In your Leads board, add columns: Client Name, Business Type, Vibe, Website URL, Video Link, Status.
    • Manually copy the Google Drive link to the Video Link column.
    • Add an automation: When Video Link added, send email to [Client Email] with template.
    • Optional: Use Zapiers free tier to auto-upload videos to Drive and log links in Monday (set up a trigger for Vercels video output).
  6. Test It:
    • Add a test client in Monday (e.g., Jos Bakery, Website URL: jo-bakery.yeahbuddy.nz).
    • Open the GitHub Pages form (https://yourusername.github.io/yeahbuddy-walkthrough), enter the URL and pages (/, /services, /about, /contact).
    • Download the video, upload to Google Drive, and log the link in Monday.
    • Send a test email to ensure the client gets the link.
